      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study performed with at least three mesh refinement levels; GCI reported for key QoIs. Gradation 2 required at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted with coarse (2.1M), medium (5.4M), and fine (12.8M) cell counts. Grid Convergence Index for shear stress magnitude at the impeller outlet was 3.2% (medium-fine pair), confirming acceptable discretization error. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable; flow rates and rotational speeds match CFD boundary conditions within 2%. Gradation 2 required.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data for the generic centrifugal pump were acquired under controlled laboratory conditions. Flow rates (2–8 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM) are documented with calibration records. Boundary condition correspondence verified within 1.5%. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., RMSE or normalised error) computed for pressure rise and hemolysis index across all operating points. Gradation 2 required.",
      "rationale": "Predicted pressure rise agreed with experimental measurements to within 8% RMSE across all 5 operating points. Relative hemolysis index predictions fell within the experimental uncertainty band for 4 of 5 conditions; the fifth deviated by 11%, which is within the accepted tolerance for MRL 2. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (shear stress, hemolysis index) directly map to the clinical endpoint of red blood cell damage. Gradation 2 required.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoIs are volume-averaged scalar shear stress and the Lagrangian hemolysis index derived from particle tracking. Both quantities are directly linked to the Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model and to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1. QoI relevance is high. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
